results.title: Fine silver key to happiness bracelet
results.description:
This silver bracelet features a curved focal plate imprinted with the words “LIVE LAUGH LOVE,” surely the keys to a happy and fulfilling life. The focal plate is made of fine silver created with Precious Metal Clay (PMC). I have added a patina to enhance the contrast of the words within the shiny silver. The plate is linked to a double curb sterling silver chain and is terminated with a sterling lobster claw clasp.  Adding to the whimsy is a tiny puffed heart charm. The focal plate measures 1/8” by 1 3/4” and the bracelet overall measures 7 1/2” in length.

Please remember most everything here is hand-made, so expect minor variations.

Precious metal clay is comprised of recycled (not mined) microscopic silver particles mixed with an organic binder. When wet, it can be molded, stamped, or formed into 3 dimensional objects. Once fired, the organic binders burn off and the resulting object is 99.9% silver. The object can be polished and oxidized (blackened) to accent details. All of my PMC items are fired at maximum temperature (1650F) for two hours to ensure they are of maximum strength and will survive years of wear. I also tumble each item with stainless steel shot to further work- harden them. Since fired PMC is fine silver, it tarnishes much more slowly than sterling silver, ensuring the finish lasts indefinitely.
